      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Chloramphenicol, a powerful antibiotic isolated in 1947 from the <i>Streptomyces venezuelae</i> bacterium, is active against a broad spectrum of bacterial infections and is particularly valuable against typhoid fever. Assign <i>R</i> or <i>S</i> configurations to the chirality centers in chloramphenicol.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcElSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--9450160a02ac9b1aecedf7501514198d86045143/OChem_05_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"The wedge-dash structure of chloramphenicol.\">",
